caption: Amer was one of the kindest people we met in our time in New Orleans! Great food and good  company.  Would 100% come back to this place.
We wasted 2.5 hours here waited for our drinks for an hour and then another hour for the food followed by 30 minutes to get the check. To top it off the food wasn’t good...
Owner was very friendly. Great food and reasonable prices.
Food was delicious.    Staff is excellent!  Love the atmosphere.
Had to wait a REALLY long time for the food.
The waiter was very friendly, the food arrived quickly, and the food was very good.

If you are in New Orleans you must go to Estrella Steak and Lobster. The staff is super friendly and chill. The food was absolutely amazing. The ribeye was perfect. BBQ shrimp peel and eat was fresh and full of flavor. The beverages were mixed just right! This place is cozy and has a great relaxed atmosphere. Don't miss out on this great seafood cocktails and exceptional service.
Steak was wafer thin and thus overcooked.  Service was mediocre
Best place hands down to eat a good Po'boy during the day or a good perfectly cooked steak with a whole lobster at night in the French Quarter
Absolutely one of the best places that I have eaten at in New Orleans.  We try to come down once a year and have a few favorites.  This place just made the list.

Just so happened to run into this place by accident and I can not say how awesome and good this place is. Hospitality is great and the food is even better. We came for brunch and will come back to try the night life. 😀
What a great little place! We enjoyed brunch twice here this past weekend. Food and service was amazing. Will definitely be back!

Best omelette I’ve ever had.
Great food, wonderful staff.

Great place to eat!  Friendly attentive service.   The caprese salad was made with fresh mozzarella and simply with basil, good tomatoes, and olive oil.  The hamburger and fries were perfectly cooked and flavorful.
We had a great time here for brunch! The service was spectacular and the food was delicious!

Great food and atmosphere
best margarita. Love this place.

We stumbled across this simple yet welcoming little spot when the wait staff stopped and introduced themselves and showed us the menu. We had New Yorks with all the trim and it was a good meal and a good time! Dessert was peach cobbler...fantastic!!
Food was great ... Had the stuffed mushrooms and crab cakes....
Our bartender Dana was great. She makes awesome cocktails with effort and attention to detail.
Great food

I don’t even know where to start.... service was GOD awful.... we were greeted by some slum lord who ran out of the kitchen trying to sell me on his BBQ since both waitress were outside drinking with their friends. Bar had minimal choices.. I have more beer in my fridge then they have in theirs.. Now to the food. I’m not from New Orleans, but I’m sure Walmart French fries covered in warmed up mushroom cream sauce isn’t traditional... the gumbo was luke warm at best with 2 pieces of shrimp.  I’d honestly say the jalapeños were the best thing on the menu. (I ignored all the red flags so I deserved it) but be like all the smart people on the street and keep walking.
I have lived in nola for two years and stumbled in last night.  Good dinner, good drinks all reasonably priced especially for the location.

Oh my God. The best food i have ever eaten. Plus the service was excellent. Plus me and my family didn't have to wait 30 minutes or more to be waited on and seated. I will definitely be going back. Thanks New Orleans 👍👍👍

Mother's Day meal was ruined. Ordered a seafood platter, but the oysters were missing. Food was raw and under cooked. It  looked as of it was rushed. I had to recook the fish and shrimp in the oven. I also had to refry the french fries. The only thing that was edible was the salad. Sorry, but I dont think I will order from here again.

As I ventured away from the craziness and fun of Bourbon street during Mardi Gras, I stumbled upon the quaintness of Estrella. The service was impeccable and the crab cakes were delicious. My Margarita was mixed with perfection. Definitely a stop I’ll make again!
Had breakfast. Seafood omlette with fried potatoes and biscuit. The omlette was ok, but the biscuit was not hot and potatoes was under cooked.
The food was okay but our waiter was very absent minded.
The food was good. There was some sort of mix up with our order so our breakfast took a bit longer to get to us than expected, but our waitress Dana was extremely nice about it. She was great.

Good food
Great food and service. Barbecue shrimp and bread pudding yum! Dwight was a great server. Quiet too.
Wish I could give 100 stars, great food and staff

Estella's has the best deal in the Quarter.  4-7 Early Bird Dinner for $19.95. Salad, entree and dessert. The steak is amazing and the Taste of New Orleans was on point! Our new 'must go to' place.

Absolutely lovely place to eat. If you want to experience the local scene and get some good mom & pop type of food with a homemade taste, this is it. This isn’t a big location, but everyone working here is overly friendly. The owner and head chef came out to check on my steak and make sure I was enjoying it. Great food, great environment. I would love to eat here again!
Great food and excellent staff.
Quite pricey for food but 5$ holy rollers? Is that worth 4 stars in the quarter? Prob not. Buy a cheapy and keep it moving
It was okay. VERY dark in there. And the food was okay. Nothing crazy great. Sever was pleasant and was the only sever there.
Yum.  So glad they were open and exactly what i was looking for as a  NOLA breakfast joint

It was aight food was good but didn't come out fast enough my steak wasnt off the grill hot or even close I almost sent it back ...waitress was ok but is obviously accustomed to ppl sticking to the menu..if I give you my order that's what I want just charge me  accordingly dont tell me what I can't have if it's on the menu ...my BlackBerry peach mojito was watered down to say the least the best part of the experience was the elderly gent at the front door whatever they pay him they should double it .
The service is amazing! Amir, Frederick and everyone made our experience perfect. The steak was cooked perfectly. We will be coming here every visit!!
Portions of chicken on po boy left a lot to be desired

We got a steak dinner, shrimp and chicken pasta. It was all pretty good. The price point was very nice, like $40 for the whole meal.  Steak was medium when I asked for rare. No big deal though. Also they didn't really put any salt/pepper on the steak or fries, so I had to shake salt on everything. But besides that, especially considering the price of the meal, we were quite pleased. Service was great, too. Waitress was very nice. So was the dude at the door that waved us in.

Me and my mother ordered a bowl of Gumbo (for $8 each), and were very unsatisfied. Not only was the soup lukewarm (barely warm at all), but there was hardly any meat in the bowl of soup. We ordered the bowl, instead of the soup, thinking that we would get a nice fair portion, but there was hardly anything in there, other then liquid soup, and it was not even hot (it was lukewarm). Also, they put a crab leg in our soup, and it had no meat in it (it was like a hollow crab leg). We did tell the waitress about it, and she offered up a piece of bread pudding to share, but it was not any good either, and again, not hot (barely lukewarm). Anyways, overall, very unsatisfied (though the waitress was very friendly). She told us the temp of the soup was normal. Anyways, the soup itself tasted very good. It is just too bad there was hardly any meat in it, and that it was not even hot (in the least bit) when she served it to us.
First po'boy ever. It was shrimp, and excellent. Drinks were also very cosmopolitan and delightful. You do pay for what you get here.

If you aren't looking you will walk past the entrance. It is not a fancy establishment,  modest furnishings,  but good service, a respectful bar, food is very good.  We had the lobsters for two, price was reasonable, not at all crowded, we would go back next time we are in NOLA.
We went for breakfast and it was wonderful.  Great service (Patrick C.), atmosphere and food.  One of those places we felt lucky to find!

Bar tender brings all the vibes. Real friendly chap with a great sense of humor and good solid knowledge of New Orleans. We only had a couple drinks at the bar - so I cannot attest for the food, but the atmosphere with the team members was great to see! Always awesome to see a team work as a cohesive unit!
Great food and Great customer service . Treated like royalty #GoNiners
I eat here Everytime I'm in New Orleans and never dissapointed

Another awesome meal in NOLA !

I went for breakfast.   The food was very bland, tasteless is more accurate.   The milk punch was awful.   The service was mediocre.   I had to ask more than once for requested items.   I was charged $2.50 for a side of milk for my coffee. It was brought in a small tin pitcher so there was no mistake in my asking for a side of milk instead of creamer for my coffee. If there is a solo reason to stop here it's the bbq shrimp! Pop that head, saver the flavor, and sit back licking your fingers wondering if it gets better. It didn't, but that shrimp was a high bar to reach but it was good. The only knock was on cleanliness of the oily plates and silverware, but you could look at it like my friend who said "it's like a well seasoned grill, that's where the extra flavoring comes from!" :D We were there at lunch and there were only a couple other tables there so we got to visit with staff a little and I really enjoyed the personalities - if you don't know what the expression "good people" means stop here when it's not busy and you'll meet good people!!!
Had brunch, omelet was watery, coffee was lukewarm,  nice women's restroom.

Do NOT  go there on a Superbowl match day, pre booked for the lobster as per on line menu, oh no, given basic menu and told lobster maybe from 4pm. Staff not remotely interested so we walked! Go at your peril!

Just left this place and not sure how they received the ratings they've received. Where do I start?  First, they ran out of both the ribeyes and strips and baked potatoes.  Second, we chose the filet mignon. Mine was supposed to be stuffed with lump crab and sauce. It was frozen "crab" cake breading and overcooked (I asked for medium, received well done) and dry.  Third, my friend ordered the crab cakes so she received the same dried, boxed ones I got.  Lastly, one in my party forgot to add a tip so the waitress made sure she asked about the missing tip. Very unprofessional.  You live and you learn but I'll never patronize this establishment when I return to NOLA.
Very poor service. Food clearly fried and not grilled as menu states. There's plenty of restaurants to choose from around and I found a bad one!

We were told we still had to pay for our meals despite the fact that there was no way any of us would be able to finish.
Awesome service and food

Despite looking like a bar from the outside, being busy with people coming in and out, it is quite spacious on the inside with great food and great service. The owner even hung out with us for a while and invited us for drinks, unfortunately we were in a hurry to catch the sights. Thank you!

The manager Amar is soooooo wonderful!! Great food,  great service,  can't recommend it more.

It was cold but not too cold

The food was some of the worst I’ve ever tasted! I had the food delivered. My delivery time kept getting pushed back, so my food was cold when it arrived. I ordered crab cakes and creamed spinach. The crab cakes were something I had never experienced before, and not In a good way. The breading was soggy and just bad. I forced myself to eat the spinach because I was hungry, it was too late to get anything else and I had just spent 20 bucks on this catastrophe. How can you mess up creamed spinach??  NOLA. Not only was the service terrible (keep in mind tip is included so they aren’t working for the tips, I would’ve left $0 if I could), the food was also not good. I ordered the biscuits and gravy which actually wasn’t too bad, but my friends ordered the all American breakfast sandwich which was supposed to have sausage, egg, cheese and potatoes.... it came with just soggy eggs and cheese. There are so many other good food places to choose from in New Orleans and I recommend going to any of them over this restaurant.

The poached eggs were cooked solid and the sauce had some weird taste to it. the waitress didn’t even notice that nothing was eaten on my plate which is a nice way off saying, GROSS! I asked the bartender what she recommended and she said “I have been here for 18 years, it all tastes the same to me”. I do not recommend eating there at all. Never again!!!!

Amazing food,  it was all delicious. The service was just great too. They are very nice and always ready to help.  I loved the music,  he is an older gentleman,  but the music was perfect and not loud, perfect ambiance for eating, talking and listen to great jazz music.

The food came out super staggered too, by the time the last person got their food, the first people were already done. Overall we were completely disgusted with the service and two of our steaks were extremely overcooked and dry.
The food oh k. I didnt like that the site says lobster nd steak and theres no lobster nor steak.....but the crab cakes are to die 4

It wasn't busy in there when we were there. Food wasn't nothing to write home about. Could've got a better quality food for much less of the price. This is a one and done for me.
Great

We had a couple of hours to kill before a show at the House of Blues, so we stopped here for a bite. First of all I want to report that the owner emeer has tried to sexually exploit his female workers I know this for a fact from a lady friend he also paid another female employee to have sex with a alcohol tax worker to keep his license he also pays a state trooper which is a friend of his for information when the excise people come in don't eat there period

We found Estrella after the concierge at our hotel recommended two other steakhouses that were far more expensive and didn't have what we wanted to eat without cobbling together something from steak and various side dishes that did not come with the steak. Estrella had what we wanted and we were even surprised by additional options that were specials not listed on the menu. The staff was extremely attentive and added special touches to our meal. The live music was very good, and the musician played multiple instruments and varied the music. Chef Frederick came to our table twice to check on our satisfaction with the meal. The steak was cooked to order and delicious. The barbequed shrimp was so good it nearly knocked me over. We wouldn't even let them take the dish the barbequed shrimp was cooked in, in case we wanted to dip some of our steak, which we did. The crawfish etoufee was the best we'd eaten in the French Quarter. And, the bartenders made a proper up Manhattan, also delicious.

I read the reviews on here and I was skeptical about whether to go or not and I am so glad I did! We went in before 6 p.m. and there was a sign out front that said early bird specials. We were able to get a 16 ounce New York strip with a potato and a salad for $18 each! It also came with delicious bread pudding! This is a small hole in the wall but everything was cooked well. There was an older gentleman playing the saxophone, the flute, the keyboard and singing. He was a one-man band and it was beautiful! I would highly recommend this restaurant. The bread they bring you out of the beginning is phenomenal!

We stopped in after seeing the special board outside but it was so dark in dreary from street we almost passed it by. The waitstaff quickly greeted us and we were brought our drink order within minutes. Our waiter went over the specials and we both selected tasty sounding options- hubby got then ribeye and I ordered the new Orleans Trio. It came with salads and fresh bread as well. Two other couples came in while were there and al complimented chef when he came out. The couple behind us got engaged while we were there and the patrons helped celebrate with them and helped take pics of them! The bread pudding the brought as part of the special was tasty and a huge portion! They need to rethink the outside sign as it is not truly appealing and might actually hurt their business ... but those that come in will be pleasantly surprised by this NOLA hidden treasure.
The food was poor. We came for steaks, but they were out. The service was okay, but owner would be not come to our table.

I'm always scepitcal when restaurants display their food outside and have someone trying to lure you in. At first, I really didn't think it was s good choice, seemed like a weird old bar/ restaurant with bad decor. Our waitress really went out of her way to make us feel welcomed and I liked that the chef at the end even stopped by to say hi. I really enjoyed the messy bbq shrimps but the steak was pretty low quality. They give you parmesan butter bread for your meal. They also gave us a free order of spinach and a great desert. Would I go back...nope but I appreciate the efforts made and maybe this might be up someone else's alley.

Vanesa was an awesome  bartender  Very cordial all while feasting on bbq shrimp .big portions  very fair prices , big mixed cocktails.

(Translated by Google) All great, welcoming place  (Original) Tutto ottimo Locale accogliente

I will never forget this place. We stumbled upon this place our first night in Nola. It was slow getting the food, but that's a plus in my eyes... Everything was being made fresh to order. Everyone in our party ordered something different, so we all shared bites. I ordered filet mignon, and it was good, but standard. The shrimp and grits were the best we had - better than what we had at Emiril's. They were perfectly creamed and the flavor of the shrimp left your mouth watering. THE RIBEYE. Oh my god, THE RIBEYE. A year later, and it's still the one steak I crave. When I think, "I'm craving steak," I'm actually craving this steak. I had one bite, and ended up eating half of my mom's plate. Perfectly cooked medium-rare. Melted like butter in my mouth. I was full, but I couldn't stop eating it. The gator balls with the roumelade were a memorable dish as well. I cannot wait to go back to New Orleans, just to eat here again.

We were greeted and seated by a wonderful gentleman who was prompt in recommendat ions and getting us the best meal true to New Orleans. Great service and the steak perfectly cooked. Those potatoes with a cream sauce topped with bacon and chives were awesome. The BBQ shrimp was delicious. Atmosphere true to New Orleans. Highly reccomend for food, service and cost.

Looked in yelp and Google for suggestions for places to eat. My friend and I were both craving steak, and Estrella had many good reviews. Unfortunately, we must not have picked a good night. I ordered a New York strip steak medium, and my friend ordered the prime rib medium rare. Both of our steaks were very well done, mine was borderline burnt. Definitely not worth the price. The service was good, but the food left much to be desired.
So far one of the best seafood places we've eaten at. The atchalaya was PHENOMENAL! Decently priced and great service and atmosphere.
Food is amazing!! Prices are very reasonable!! Service outstanding!!! Got the Cucumber Basil Lemonade cocktail is so refreshing and sooo good!!!

Worst Bloody Mary I had ever. Tasted like pure tomato juice. Terrible service- only 1 other table full besides ours and could not get a refill of water. My ribeye had zero flavor and was undercooked. My lobster tail was cold and the shrimp etoufee was bland. I am beyond disappointed that I wasted a vacation dinner on this place and hope you choose to never go!!
Amazing steak! And they allowed me to get the food to-go. Great.
I ordered the prime rib and my husband had the hamburger and we shared the loaded fries. We were absolutely loved it. We had live entertainment and great service. We would definitely go back.
Great food !! Had lobster last night good price will go back

We love searching for local "joints" that bring a home town flavor that is outside of the box of the chain restaurants.  Sooooo, we found Estrella's on-line and walked to the establishment from our hotel.  It is right passed the House of Blues and upon entry we were greeted by a friendly doorman and the most OUTSTANDING server ever!  His name...Assante!  My god he was probably the kindest, funniest and sincere waiter I have ever had.  I like to highlight the staff, because they are the life blood of a eatery and will determine your overall experience.  With that said, the food was amazing!  You must try the STAR-TINI and the Cucumber Lemonade.  Upon tasting those drinks you will change your religion.  Alas, the food, yes...the FOOD was exceptional.  My steak was unreal!  The fish dishes were incredible and the garlic-honey sauce concoction was absolutely delish!  Oh, and DO NOT forget to order the bread pudding for desert.  There was a one man band, playing the flute, sax and singing.  An older gentleman, who despite his age played some swanky tunes. The owner was in and checked on us and again it was Assante who made the evening.  What a great introduction to New Orleans!  Thank you.

Just a lovely dining experience..great drinks .the bartender made us a black cherry peach mojito ,it was delicious.she then orderd me and my husband a delicious barbique shrimp along with a blackened catfish which was huge .It was very tasty .We will be back next time for the live maine lobster and crabcakes.great service

To be honest my new fiancé, Kelsey, and I were on our way to a different restaurant for dinner and asked a worker from another local restaurant where we should go and he immediately said Estrella's. We wandered over and it has been by far the best experience we've had here yet. We were immediately greeted by the owner, Amir. I was in the mood for some seafood gumbo and Kelsey does not like seafood so she asked what they had for options. He said they could make her whatever she wanted. One of their burgers caught here eye but then she had a special request because she likes her burgers very smashed and flat. Amir did not bat and eyelash and as he was saying they could do that, his head chef walked by so Amir told him about the unusual request and he seemed happy to do it. The gumbo was best I've had in the NOLA and Kelsey was very happy with the burger. The atmosphere was incredible. They had a live musician playing jazz in the background. I can't even begin to describe how great the experience was. We felt like we were the only ones in there but at the same time were overjoyed every time where heard Amir clanking a spoon on a plate to get everyone's attention to make an announcement of what other patrons were celebrating. One table was celebrating a wedding, one just found out they were pregnant, and we had just got engaged. While in the bathroom Kelsey asked about a desert menu and Amir asked if he could surprise us and she said yes and I'm sure glad she did. He brought out a beautiful plate that had samples bread pudding, cheesecake, and a piece of chocolate cake. The bread pudding was our favorite followed closely by the cheesecake and the chocolate cake. A trip to the NOLA will never happen again without going to Estrella's. I hope if you ever dine in this gem that you have the pleasure of doing so while Amir is present. His hospitality is unmatched.
Great authentic NO atmosphere, friendly and timely wait staff, steaks and filet cooked to perfection and great prices!!!
Excellent service and excellent food. Made my trip to New Orleans.
The food and service were great.
Service is a relaxed pace, but the food and atmosphere make it all better. If you're in a hurry give yourself more time it's worth it!!!!

Food was between OK and good. Prices very high. Two people, Lobster tail and grilled red fish with lobster bisque & gator bites for appetizers (No Drinks) $90.00. Lobster bisque was good but NOT the  lobster bisque you normally get. My only description would be it's kind of like a Cajun lobster bisque. Lobster tail (2 tails) were about the 6 oz size. They were OK but lacked any real sweetness you normally taste with lobster. Huge loaded baked potato done just right. Good Jazz musician.
Awesome !  Ribeye ribeye ribeye !!
Absolutely horrible food, ridiculous prices and the service was mediocre. 1 person from our party of 6 actually ate their food and liked it. We will never return
Red beans and rice - super delicious!!! Tilapia & crab cake dinner was plentiful and tasty. Live jazz created smooth atmosphere.
Great service, wonderful atmosphere and the food was awesome. Carrie Berry was the best. Will be back!!!!!

Known this place since it was Star. Steakhouse.  It was 4* then, can't be very far from it now.The food has always been ROCKIN & certainly worth it. Sizeable portions plus.. Love being Southern. THANK GOD!

The oyster Rockefeller po boy was great
Perfect!!!!
It is a wonderful place to have dinner you don't feel rushed it has great jazz great service with great drinks I would bring my friends back here again and again

The service was terrible, the restaurant was blazing hot in the middle of may and it took us over 45 minutes to get a Cesar salad and a piece of CHEWY blackened catfish and overcooked broccoli. the entire time we were waiting on our food, our server never checked on us or refilled our drink. our server had no idea what the sides were on the dishes. and the pimms cup i ordered was a totally horiffic butchering of a classic cocktail. we really should have known better when the wait  at every other restaurant was 45 minutes and we walked right in and sat down. the restaurant wasnt even full and the bar was empty and our service was still subpar at a restaurant in a city that prides itself on the service industry.
Don't get the tuna.

I love the great food especially the bbq shrimp and if you dont know already..  its not really barbequed, its New Orleans style and in a yummy spicy sauce that you will want to dip the delicious garlic bread in. Great Steak, Lobster and really loved the Fettuccini Alfredo! All of the staff is welcoming and takes real good care of you. I especially love the owner Amer, the bartender Lori, the waitress Carrie and the wonderful guys greeting at the door Mr. Bobby and Skeeter. I will definitely be back!
FIne and interesting cooking
Expensive compare to the food and service quality

This place was a nightmare. I called for reservation on a Saturday night, knowing it might be tough to get in. He said sure, , but not until 9 pm. We got there at 8:25, it was half empty and they seated us right away. Then we waited. And waited. It took 25 minutes, 2 servers, and 3 tries to get our simple drink order right. I asked for bread after a half an hour, (when we were finally ordering) and server came back and practically threw it on the table. At this point I was disgusted and seriously worried about the quality of the food, so I got up to leave. While I was trying to convince my hubby that we should pay for our "drinks" and leave, our food came out. He wasn't happy either, but he was afraid to walk out. He ordered steak and I ordered prime rib, but they both looked the same. His order came out without his baked potato, was told it would be out soon. My potato looked shriveled and brown. I said "no, nope, and we walked. I would never have done that before (actually, I don't know because I've never had such an awful experience), but I'm too old to put up with poor service AND bad food! Especially in New Orleans!
Amazing food! My steak melted in my mouth. Service is phenomenal!  Loved our experience.

To call these the best drinks in New Orleans is too much of an understatement. There aren't enough words to describe our wonderful experience at Estrella! But, I will certainly tell you that we will not be back to New Orleans without visiting this beautiful place at last twice a trip. Amer was an absolute joy and runs a beautiful establishment with an atmosphere that is unmatched. The service was fast, gracious, interactive, and the highlight of our trip. Please go  And try Kevin's Cucumber Basil Lemonade - it will change your life. (This coming from a cucumber hater.) The experience is unmatched and the people are to die for. Will always go back every single time. Thank you, Amer!

We went in and sat down and ordered. We sat for over an hour with no communication from owner or staff about what was happening with our order.  After hearing from other around that the owner and staff were fighting we left. I only gave 1 star cause its the only way to warn others!!!
Fun atmosphere with a lovely staff! Pleasant quick stop in the mix of all the parade fun.
Would give it 5 Stars if the price was a little lower, service was great and the Taste of New Orleans was the bomb!

This was our must do dinner place every Mardi Gras but the last 5 years or so it has been going down hill fast-just had our last dinner there. Food is now so-so and service was worse. Too MANY other choices so pass this up. Real shame as it used to be so, so good.
Good service reasonable prices. Good food.
Excellent Place to Eat, for all !   Estrella Steak & Lobster House

This place was so quiet, but we came in around 5pm. The food was EXCELLENT!!!. Filet mignon cooked to perfection,  Appetizer, I had stuffed mushrooms, husband had Cajun nuggets. Absolutely wonderful. Came here last year, excellent then too. Best meal we've had in Nola. Laurie, our waitress, GREAT!!! Don't miss this place
Did not keep the reservation, took over an hour to be seated, and my steak was cold and undercooked. To top it off the service was poor.

These good reviews have to be a fluke.  This place is a joke.  I was not over charged like some of the others.  They probably only do that to people that are visibly drunk. It is very dark and dirty.  Cobwebs hanging from the ceiling.  They also appear not to have a liquor license, but that doesn't stop who appeared to be a manager from pouring himself a drink. Terrible service, waitress forgot to put in my sons order and then claimed that they didn't have the grilled cheese that was on the kids menu.  Who doesn't have bread and cheese?  My wife's steak was barely edible, very dry.  It was also about half of the size the menu stated.  Do yourself a favor and avoid this place.

Incredible lobster. The Lobster for Two is an amazing deal, with two lobsters, two salads, two sides, and a generous helping of delicious bread pudding for $49.99. Their lobster bisque is to die for. Only reason it wasn't a 5 is because they didn't have any alcohol due to a liquor license transition.

The food was delicious. We were greeted at in a timely fashion at the door. The manager that has been there for 17 years had to be our waitress because a no show of a waitress and she  executed the role. Great table service

Horrible service, we were the only ones being waited on and she still couldn't get my order correctly. The food was over-priced and I could of made it better myself at home. And they don't serve any alcohol.
I absolutely Love the Star. Great food, people, and atmosphere. Love to drink a little wine and listen to some music. I highly recommend this place. It is truly a great dining experience.

We absolutely enjoyed food there, if you are looking for authentic home made kitchen food then you have to go for it.  Don't forget to bring your cash and wine. They don't accept credit cards and don't sell alcohol.

Food was awful as was the service.  The waitress did not even take our drink order and when prompted to she informed us the they did not have alcoholic beverages but if we so desired we could walk to the corner and he friends work there we could get a drink and bring it back.  When we asked to spilt the check as we had four people dinning she said I can't do that but if we did the math she could enter the amounts?????. The filet was poor a poor cut and way under cooked and the sauce tasted like hormel brown gravy out of a pack and that was on top of the stuffed filet just plain awful and did I mention it cost $46 and only came with one side no salad or soup???? The bread was cheap French bread soaked in some kind of cooking oil and doused in Parmesan cheese and wrapped in bounty paper towels. PLEASE!!!!! Don't make the same mistake we did.... This may seem a little unbelievable but it is one hundred percent true.
We ate here because of the good reviews. I was very disappointed and surprised. The restaurant was dirty. Staff was sloppy in service and appearance. Food was so so. Would not recommend.

Overall, I would definitely eat there again!  The entrance and appearance are that it is just a hole in the wall. Although the decorations and furniture are nothing exciting, the dining area was clean.  We are here for lunch. The place only had maybe 5 tables occupied and a few at the bar. The one waiter was able to sufficiently serve everyone. He was lively, attentive, and gave advice about menu items.  We tried the "Taste of New Orleans" and a shrimp appetizer. The entire meal was excellent! What a delicious surprise for this hole in the wall. What a treat!

Sitting in tropical isle about to throw up. My stomach feels really bad after eating the New York Strip. I have a very strong stomach and something about this meal was not right. Worst $100 meal I've ever had. Sorry. Good service though.
Supremely atmospheric, nice place to just hang out and enjoy a drink. Their lobster stuffed filet mignon is amazing though.

We LOve this place!  It's full of local color. The lobster dinner is outstanding....the cream spinach hmmmm great.  The wait staff has always been wonderful and s large part of the atmosphere.  The bartender makes this drink called the blackberry or black cherry and peach monitor... My new favorite drink!   Oh and the bread pudding is the best.   I highly recommend  this place!

Came down to nola for a long weekend and wanted to find a more local place for dinner. Food was great. Blackened ribeye was one of the best Ive had in a while. Good music too. Staff was nice, kept drinks full. Food had great local flavor with good prices. Only issue was the server forgot to put in an order of jambalaya so it came out late. Other then that it was a great restaurant. Would definitely go back.
It was a wonderful experience! The food was great, the music was really nice, the dessert was wonderful and the service was on point...Lori is awesome :)
Excellent service. Excellent food. Highly recommended.  We all got something different and everyone enjoyed the meal. Definitely will return on my next trip to New Orleans.
Amazing food! The lobster for 2 is well worth it!
Lobster (4 tails) 2 happy boys
Unfortunately I cannot give a good review.  The service was good but my steak was very cold and overpriced.  I may give it a second shot but it will be a tough decision.

Good food and a great atmosphere! We came here last year and called ahead this time to ask them to save us the same booth in the back. Not only did they save it for us, but the owner, Amir, gave us the red carpet treatment. After a great evening and a bottle of wine, we asked Amir to call us a cab. He got us the cab, personally walked us out, and told the cabbie to take care of us. Good people!

My favorite spot in the quarter to have a steak. I have been eating here for many years and look forward to getting back to town to enjoy the blackened ribeye, baked oyster combo and a great wine. If you haven't been here...you owe it to yourself to go.

If I could give this place a quarter star I would.  I normally don't post but after having a horrible experience,  I feel the need to warn others so they are not fooled by these reviews. My fiance had the steak which was good but medium rare not medium well. They were out of crab cakes so they gave him shrimp. He said that they tasted like sand. I got the lobster tails. It was rubbery and did not taste good. I did not feel well at all when I got home. The waitress was barely there to place our order and pay for it. When we saw the bill we realized why. They had put down the gratitudy as 18% which I would have given 5%. The only part I want to commend were the bus boys. They were courteous and efficient.  I wish they could have gotten the 185 gratitudy.

I had the opportunity to enjoy one of the best prepared filet and lobster dishes that could be found. in  New Orleans. I learned it was prepared by an up and coming Chef,  Khalid Robiho. I do not hesitate to use the word..... Amazing

FANTASTIC   stopped in for a drink had a great time. The staff was a blast. We didn't have a chance to have a meal this time but definetly will next time inNew Orleans We did have appies and the crab cakes were to die for
Food was so good. And the waiter was very nice.

We called ahead and they had a 45 minute wait and when we got there they had one table on the sidewalk available so we snagged it. The fact that we didn't have to wait too long for dinner helped, but overall the lettuce/spinach was soggy in the salad and the burger I ordered was just ok.  Did not go for either the steak or the lobster since we wanted a quicker meal.  The owner waited on us and he was very pleasant, but otherwise it was just below average.
Disappointed by the poor quality of the food. Would not go back. The stuffed filet mignon was dry and flavorless.

So disappointed at this restaurant. I went here for a birthday dinner and was treated so horrible and not as if I was a paying customer. The waitress had a attitude when she found out that a few of my guests were not going to be in attendance do to their jobs and kids. She was on the phone the whole time she served us and I only seen her about 3-4 times. The person who cater to us the most was the busser and treated us with the upmost respect. She sat at the bar on the phone or would leave out and go walk on the phone. My food was not good like it was my prior times going there. When asked to speak to a manager they could not find one because she was out of the restaurant hanging on Decatur drinking. When they finally found her, she came in asked what was the problem and when we stated the problem she became offensive and yelling and screaming at us as if we were nothing. I have worked in the hospitality businesses and never once seen this type of action coming from a person of management. Never in my life have I been to a establishment and was spoken to as if I was a piece of trash. When we became offensive to her and how she spoke to us she stated she was going to call the police on us. All we wanted to do was express our complaints and pay our bill and they took it totally out of control. From the waitress yelling at us to the owners. They were not dealing with children but young professionals who all have paying jobs and work for big companies. For me as the birthday girl to be treated with such disgust I will never go back to that establishment and will never recommend it to anyone.
Had the steak and lobster....it was great. The drink and jazz music were awesome!

Unfortunately, my husband and I were sorely disappointed, to say the very least, with our experience last night at Star Steak and Lobster House. We were in NO celebrating our 41st anniversary, and we were so looking forward to eating there. We have been there before, and the food, martinis, service, and prices were always outstanding; however, last night's dining experience was less than satisfying.  First, the service was very slow.  No one came to our table for a while, and when the waitress did come, the size of the martinis was much smaller than what we had in our previous experiences.  The "lump" crabmeat was terrible!!! It appeared to be canned crabmeat, and not only did it taste very strong, but it was also shredded, not lump, was brown, and had a strong aroma.  Neither of us ate it.  The worst part about the experience was that I was fired up about getting the whole Maine lobster, which is their signature dish, but they had "just sold the last fresh lobster" before I placed my order. This was at 7:00 on a Friday night!!! We should have left right then, but we have never done that before. I was asked if I wanted two lobster tails, but when I asked if they were frozen, the waitress said YES.  I opted for the filet mignon with the lump crabmeat, very reluctantly. My hushand ordered a filet stuffed with crabmeat and crawfish, which is what he wanted in the first place. The steaks were cooked to perfection, but neither of us ate the seafood for the reason stated above.  The crawfish were tiny--definitely not Louisiana crawfish--and rubbery.The sides of sauteed spinach and asparagus were good.  The good thing in the end was that the waitress brought out a steamed lobster tail alongside my steak at no charge, which was good, and we got two martinis, at no extra charge. We did leave a generous tip to thank the staff for their efforts to please us after all.

My husband and I have been to Star Steak and Lobster twice. Once on our honeymoon last year and earlier this year. We are planning a trip for this weekend and will visit again! Our trips to NOLA will always include Star Steak and Lobster from now on. We have gone both times with a Groupon deal and have had no trouble. The servers and staff at Star Steak and Lobster are always friendly and the food is incredible! We have recommended Star Steak and Lobster to several friends and family members. We love the relaxed atmosphere and live music. Groupon or no Groupon, this is a must on any list for a New Orleans trip!

So we had the GROUPON deal....lets just say they don't want you to use this. They first do not tell you they add on fees for using them. When we asked the waitress SARA about this then she had a major attitude and started yelling "if you want to give me a $5 tip then I can just give it to the bar tender." First of all we were not only giving her a $5 tip we were giving her the remainder of the money for our bill which was $25 for  the additional $22 owed in the folder with the bill. Where I  am from then you leave the tip for the waitress on the table and not with the bill or hand it to the waitress, which is what I was going to do. She was getting real nasty and my husband who likes to prevent conflict encouraged me not to, but I HAD to get back with her because I am not sure who she thought she was talking to us in that manner. I told her she should never be a waitress again and should be fired on the spot because that is no way to provide service and just to assume that the amount we gave for the bill was just her tip (considering we were still sitting at the table and handing her a $20 bill starting the  hand it to her when she started all of this for her tip). I am sorry if other GROUPNERS do not tip, but just because you have one doesn't mean you cant tip. We use GROUPON to try new restaurants that we otherwise would not think of, not to rip off waitresses. Aside from the nasty attitude of SARA who should NEVER waitress again....I can say that the manager and the host who we interacted with were pleasant along with the bartender. The food was pretty good along with the jazz musician for the night who we tipped $50 for his god music. Loved the old New Orleans atmosphere. SARA YOU SHOULD BE FIRED!!! And you need to grow up and never work as a waitress in any restaurant again. This is coming from someone who often tries hard to help others advance their careers and would usually never want someone fired.

Went there to eat a non-fancy dinner, and ordered surf and turf. Fortunately there was no loud music, Brits abroad or other kalabalik. The decor is a bit cheesy and the place is dark like some watering hole, so this doesn't exactly suggest haute cuisine. But, I was positively surprised about the food, even if it was rather simple. First, I was served a loaf of bread, airy and light, topped with butter and parmesan. Then, while not a lobster expert, the lobster was tender and flavorful. The steak was cooked medium as I wanted, but was a bit oversalted. Didn't like the shrimp as much, a bit too strong flavors, although de gustibus non est disputandum. Service was good, the waitress checked me a couple of times and the glass of water was kept full. The price was not cheap, I paid $60. Overall, this is more than you would expect from a bistro, but not there yet if it aims to be a fine restaurant. It would be a good place to go eat some casual dinner.

The food and decor is horrible! I ordered the filet minion and I received a steak but it was not filet minion. It looked and tasted more like a chuck steak. The wine-mushroom sauce was terrible and tasted like gravy from a frozen Salisbury  steak tv dinner.  The potatoes were from a box with no taste but a flaky consistency.  My husband ordered bbq gulf shrimp and there was nothing bbq about them. They tasted like plastic and were chewy like rubber.  Neither of us finished our meals. This restaurant is trying to have an upscale appeal but is failing miserably. Cheap silverware, plates and glasses.  It felt a little like eating in a cafeteria. The decor is so cheesy! Pictures of Mammy and other actors who no doubt never set foot inside the building. At $20+ per plate I expect more class.

Horrible!!! I've never had a filet or lobster that was so tough! After being seated had to wait 20 minutes to place our drink order. Then when we finally ordered and received our meal I have never been more disappointed. I would never eat here or recommend this place to anyone!!!

If I had known it would take an hour and a half to get our food, I would have chosen another restaurant. Our server, Penny, only came to check on us twice, and apparently forgot to put our order in completely until we asked where our food was. The lady and gentleman who appear to own the place passed our table more than a dozen times as we were seated RIGHT in front of the kitchen, and could seem to have cared less. We ended up canceling our order and going some place else. What a disappointment. I hope Groupon gives us a refund.

Was a little chaotic at 8:00 pm. Sat at the bar, had a drink, enjoyed the NO atmosphere, conversed with "Joey", it was fun! Tuna appetizer was excellent, stuffed mushrooms good. Medium rare filet with bernaise - very good. Music was a bit loud, but fit the atmosphere, service - very good. Our party of 4 enjoyed the meal and will be back!
Nice place for lunch. Very good blackened catfish.  Friendly staff.

Disappointed. Went here years ago (many times) and loved it then--we couldn't wait to get back to NOLA just to have the surf and turf. On this last trip, the steak was outstanding; however, while I've never had a TV dinner lobster, I would imagine that's what it would taste like. Worst lobster I've ever had. Maybe we'll have better luck next time.
Great filet mignon.  The waiter was a real nice guy.  Great cozy atmosphere too.  Highly recommend this restaurant.
Food was good steak not cooked to order.I asked for medium well I got medium rare. And what kind of steak house serves steak with a butter knife.

This place is wonderful. My husband took me there for my birthday. The crab cakes were great, and the steaks were even better. The waiter was really nice and funny. The had a guy playing live music with all kinds of instruments and he was funny. We love this place, and we told each other that this would be our special occasion place. We love it.
